Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.26,0:00:12.01,Main,,0,0,0,,I will make your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.69,0:00:23.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if it meant hurting someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.36,0:00:28.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if it meant hurting myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.86,0:00:36.08,Main,,0,0,0,,So please, when your wish comes true...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.72,0:00:56.51,Main,,0,0,0,,...I wish for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.52,0:00:59.14,Main,,0,0,0,,...to smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.62,0:01:20.66,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The truth rests solely on{\i0}\N{\i1}the front/back of a card{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.66,0:01:25.96,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It has not yet been solved{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.96,0:01:35.97,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Upon the dazzling, dizzying stage,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.97,0:01:47.31,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}destroy those entangled emotions{\i0}\N{\i1}as many times as it takes to satisfy you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.31,0:01:52.53,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What should the tomorrows{\i0}\N{\i1}wandering after fate's beckoning{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.53,0:01:57.91,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}choose and discard so that{\i0}\N{\i1}they can become one?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.91,0:02:03.37,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't afford to disclose my reproachable hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.37,0:02:08.46,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The days spent draining{\i0}\N{\i1}the already-dry sea of regret{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.46,0:02:13.88,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}desire within limited words forgiveness{\i0}\N{\i1}for the unplanned smile{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.88,0:02:18.76,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't mind forgetting reality{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.76,0:02:23.89,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't want to know anything now{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.89,0:02:25.15,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:36.03,Main,,0,0,0,,You're kidding me?\NIona's playing WIXOSS too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.82,0:02:40.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, WIXOSS is fun, really!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.12,0:02:41.91,Main,,0,0,0,,"What We're Into"\NI even bought a starting deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.91,0:02:45.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Ah, but isn't this stuff only\Nfor the guys or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.67,Main,,0,0,0,,"Daikichi Apartments"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:38.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back Ru-{\i1}chan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.34,0:03:39.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.35,0:03:50.73,Main,,0,0,0,,"Kominato"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:53.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm back, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:00.57,Main,,0,0,0,,--Long time no see, Bro!\N--Hey, Ruko.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:01.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:04.16,Main,,0,0,0,,C'mon, at least put your bag away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.88,0:04:16.67,Main,,0,0,0,,It looks like it's going to be\Nan apartment. Grandma wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.67,0:04:22.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I though it was going to be a business.\NNow I have to clean the bath for one week...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:27.68,Main,,0,0,0,,They're both the same\Nin that it's just a big pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.68,0:04:29.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Big pillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.02,0:04:34.69,Main,,0,0,0,,When that's finished, it means that a\Nbig pillar is going to fit in that alley, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.69,0:04:36.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Pillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.24,0:04:39.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.40,0:04:41.99,Main,,0,0,0,,See, if a pillar goes there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.75,0:04:52.17,Main,,0,0,0,,I feel like this city is\Ngoing to just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.46,0:05:01.68,Main,,0,0,0,,All right! Grandma, that stage\Nyou custom made was really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.68,0:05:03.68,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess it's about time for a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.68,0:05:05.14,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll help too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:10.27,Main,,0,0,0,,You just came home,\Nso get yourself relaxed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.27,0:05:14.40,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right. You just left\Nyour bag there too... Ah! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:18.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Heh, you deserved that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:27.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Wha?! It stinks here! Bro!\NTake your socks off before you get in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.83,0:05:29.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.33,0:05:33.21,Main,,0,0,0,,No! I'm going to catch athlete's foot\Nall over! I'll help you after all, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:35.38,Main,,0,0,0,,It's so lively with your brother around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.38,0:05:38.25,Main,,0,0,0,,But, I don't like the place stinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.51,0:05:46.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Seeing me all the way out here,\Nyou really do like me, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.85,0:05:53.19,Main,,0,0,0,,That's not it! My favorite milk tea is at\Nthe vending machine around here, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.19,0:05:57.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Ruko, don't make Grandma too worried, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.40,0:05:58.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.98,0:06:04.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma was telling me that you haven't\Nmade friends yet after moving to this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:07.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't really need any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.57,0:06:11.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, you're pretty bold,\Nso I'm not worried that much,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.00,0:06:15.42,Main,,0,0,0,,but Grandma is worried about you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:21.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.01,0:06:22.01,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:23.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Just take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.84,0:06:31.22,Main,,0,0,0,,My work buddy told me these\Ncards are a hit with the girls now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.22,0:06:34.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I've seen some in my class playing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.19,0:06:39.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Use this to get in with everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.49,0:06:49.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm making Grandma worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:50.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, see ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.35,0:07:11.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it cold out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.68,0:07:18.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Coldy-coldy. Warmy-warmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.19,0:07:26.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, ah, I'm going to go and study now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.87,0:07:31.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"Ruko"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.04,0:07:43.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't really care too much for friends,\Nbut making Grandma worried is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.80,0:07:52.89,Main,,0,0,0,,The card called an LRIG is\Nthe player's avatar... Is it this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:08:00.56,Main,,0,0,0,,She's so cute! Um, on the\Nplayer's turn, this card...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:08.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Her voice is so cute too... Wait, what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.17,0:08:23.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.13,0:08:26.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0}? Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.55,0:08:28.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.18,0:08:34.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you fall down, Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.05,0:08:36.31,Main,,0,0,0,,You... don't hear that voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.31,0:08:38.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.73,0:08:42.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Am I the only one who can hear her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:45.73,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, so you can go now.\NI have to get back to my studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:50.65,Main,,0,0,0,,--Grandma, you can take a bath first, okay?\N--Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:53.66,Main,,0,0,0,,It's cold, so make sure you\Nkeep yourself warm in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:55.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.34,0:09:11.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.16,0:09:37.37,Main,,0,0,0,,No! It's disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.58,0:09:45.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't make it disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:22.21,Main,,0,0,0,,It's all because of that strange voice of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.04,0:10:29.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.67,0:10:32.88,Main,,0,0,0,,--Why is a card able to speak?\N--Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:36.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle? You mean you want to have a card battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.08,0:11:04.08,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't eat right? You're made out of paper.\NIf you eat, the noodles will just make you wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:06.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.50,0:11:09.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, even if you tell that to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.88,0:11:19.22,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a bit hard to ask here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.60,0:11:26.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. Their cards don't\Ntalk like you, right? I wonder why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:27.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:28.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:35.70,Main,,0,0,0,,You're a Selector, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.70,0:11:39.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Selector?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.16,0:11:41.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Found your LRIG!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:44.37,Main,,0,0,0,,You can hear her voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:46.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:49.88,Main,,0,0,0,,I have an LRIG too, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.25,0:11:52.80,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.80,0:11:54.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Come at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Come at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:09.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Perfect! No one's around!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.10,0:12:14.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Your card, Hanayo-{\i1}san,{\i0}\Nisn't like my card at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:17.32,Main,,0,0,0,,She doesn't purr like a cat,\Nand speaks normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:22.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Ruko-{\i1}san{\i0}, was it?\NSo you can hear Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s voice too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:24.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? You can't hear her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.66,0:12:31.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not a Selector after all. I have\NYuzuki speak in place of Hanayo-{\i1}san {\i0}instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.50,0:12:33.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Selector?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:34.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.96,0:12:40.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Selectors are WIXOSS players who\Nare striving to be the "Eternal Girl."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:41.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Eternal?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:45.35,Main,,0,0,0,,If you win in battle,\Nthe Selector can become their ideal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.35,0:12:47.98,Main,,0,0,0,,That form is what an "Eternal Girl" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:50.31,Main,,0,0,0,,You mean their wishes come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.31,0:12:51.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.77,0:12:54.94,Main,,0,0,0,,To be specific, that's a bit wrong there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:59.15,Main,,0,0,0,,You become a person who can make the\Nmost outrageous wishes or dreams come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.15,0:13:02.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Make wishes come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.37,0:13:07.37,Main,,0,0,0,,To have any dreams and wishes\Nbe fulfilled is just a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:15.17,Main,,0,0,0,,But, these cards can make that happen.\NFor that, you need to continue winning in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.17,0:13:21.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Yet, not everyone has a deck which\Nhas LRIGs with a mind of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.26,0:13:25.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Only the chosen girls, the Selectors, have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.35,0:13:28.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Recently, famous people such as\Nfemale celebrities and sports players
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.18,0:13:32.64,Main,,0,0,0,,"Everyone's playing this during their breaks"\Nmade announcements that they're playing WIXOSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.64,0:13:37.69,Main,,0,0,0,,They're just looking for Selectors,\Nletting others know they own an LRIG too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.11,0:13:41.99,Main,,0,0,0,,But, don't forget this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:45.99,Main,,0,0,0,,If you lose 3 times in battle,\Nyou lose your right to be a Selector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:47.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Your right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.45,0:13:50.83,Main,,0,0,0,,The moment you lose your\N3rd battle, we disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.83,0:13:53.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Your wishes won't come true,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:57.88,Main,,0,0,0,,and the world of WIXOSS, where you\Nbattle to be the Eternal Girl, will close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:14:01.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NOkay then! Ruko, let's battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:05.18,Main,,0,0,0,,But, I don't have any wishes now, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:09.22,Main,,0,0,0,,That's okay! As long as we can battle,\Nit doesn't matter if you have a wish or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:12.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle! Battle! Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:16.44,Main,,0,0,0,,See? She wants to fight too,\Nso come on, just one battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.44,0:14:18.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:19.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:23.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Yuzuki, isn't it too sudden to battle\Nwhen she doesn't know the rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.28,0:14:27.70,Main,,0,0,0,,No mercy! I'm gonna win this\Nbefore she gets to know the rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:29.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Open!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.90,0:14:59.36,Main,,0,0,0,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.15,0:15:02.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.53,0:15:03.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:05.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.66,0:15:08.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Yuzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:15.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Great! I get to go first!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:21.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay then! It's your turn now, Ruko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.88,0:15:24.88,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by "turn"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.22,0:15:28.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Kazuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:38.15,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just like the rules. Summon a SIGNI,\Ncall out the name of your LRIG, and then attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.15,0:15:42.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Kazuki! Why are you on Ruko's side?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.27,0:15:45.36,Main,,0,0,0,,He can't hear your voice from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.36,0:15:46.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Call her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.70,0:15:50.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Name? Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:55.66,Main,,0,0,0,,T-Tama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.66,0:15:57.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Why "Tama"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.66,0:16:02.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, she makes sounds like the\Ncat I used to own with Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:04.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Tama!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.55,0:16:11.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll give it a try! Level 1, Grow,\Nsummoning a SIGNI! Tama, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:14.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Tama!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.65,0:16:26.99,Main,,0,0,0,,It's gone... It's really gone! Is it okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:31.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Relax, it's only a game.\NIt'll recover at the next battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.49,0:16:34.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Recover? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.45,0:16:39.83,Main,,0,0,0,,See what you've done, Kazuki?! I could've\Nwon this easy if she didn't know the rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:45.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me too, Yuzuki?\NI don't think this is fair after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:49.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Aren't the battles supposed\Nto be fair and square?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.26,0:16:54.68,Main,,0,0,0,,It should be even more so, especially if\Nthis is a battle to make your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.68,0:16:56.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Level 3, Grow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.15,0:17:07.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Battle! Fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.82,0:17:10.65,Main,,0,0,0,,T-Tama?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.65,0:17:12.99,Main,,0,0,0,,More! Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.16,0:17:19.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Why? Why is she so strong even though\Nshe's just started? If this keeps up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:22.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yuzuki! You want to\Nbe beat here or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.58,0:17:24.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.25,0:17:27.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself! You said that\Nyou wanted to make Kazuki your own...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.55,0:17:33.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Noooooo! D-Don't say that!\NHanayo-{\i1}san{\i0}! {\i1}Hanayo-san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:35.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Both of you! Get back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:50.36,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you kids doing? Lunch is over!\NHurry and get back to class!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.36,0:17:51.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.65,0:17:56.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, wait a moment. What happens to that battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.20,0:18:02.00,Main,,0,0,0,,If an external influence terminates the battle,\Nlosses are not counted. It's a no-gamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.00,0:18:04.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.00,0:18:06.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, about that earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.88,0:18:08.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Ah! Let's go, Kazuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.00,0:18:09.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, um, laters!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.34,0:18:19.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, that was weird, wasn't it, Tama?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.02,0:18:23.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.14,0:18:28.57,Main,,0,0,0,,She's been sleeping all\Nthe way since. She's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.61,0:18:32.53,Main,,0,0,0,,So cute, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.66,0:18:42.25,Main,,0,0,0,,They use up their powers in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.25,0:18:47.46,Main,,0,0,0,,When the battle ends, they usually just sleep.\NIt's the same with Hanayo-{\i1}san {\i0}too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.46,0:18:50.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Yuzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.59,0:18:53.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Um? Isn't Kazuki-{\i1}kun {\i0}around?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.30,0:18:56.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Just because we're twins,\Nwe're not always together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.85,0:19:01.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, can you not say anything about that earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.27,0:19:02.39,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.39,0:19:04.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop playing dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.18,0:19:06.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I really don't know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.61,0:19:16.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, do you want to come over to my house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.53,0:19:22.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.16,0:19:24.50,Main,,0,0,0,,H-Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.50,0:19:26.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Can we play at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.50,0:19:30.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. Oh, Grandma's got\Nsomething to do, so I'm stepping out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:33.13,Main,,0,0,0,,You can take the rice crackers too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.18,0:19:38.80,Main,,0,0,0,,"Ruko"\NI see. So you really didn't hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.80,0:19:43.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. So you really didn't hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.10,0:19:45.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:47.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, there goes all that worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.94,0:19:54.19,Main,,0,0,0,,The thing you didn't want me\Nto know is your wish, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.19,0:19:55.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.74,0:20:00.66,Main,,0,0,0,,A wish that I want to come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.66,0:20:07.41,Main,,0,0,0,,A wish that can't be fulfilled\Njust by doing your best or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.41,0:20:08.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Yuzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.96,0:20:11.84,Main,,0,0,0,,But, since I encountered\NWIXOSS and Hanayo-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.84,0:20:16.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I now know things like miracles can happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:18.18,Main,,0,0,0,,If so, I want to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.18,0:20:21.47,Main,,0,0,0,,With the miracle granted from WIXOSS,\NI want to be the Eternal Girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.47,0:20:23.68,Main,,0,0,0,,and have another miracle fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:26.39,Main,,0,0,0,,A miracle granted by the cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.39,0:20:31.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Well then. Let's battle again.\NI'll lose to you, Yuzuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.65,0:20:35.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in this\NEternal Girl thing anyways.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.19,0:20:37.07,Main,,0,0,0,,That's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.07,0:20:42.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I mean, if Kazuki ends up hating me for that,\Nthen that already defeats the purpose of my wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:44.99,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.99,0:20:46.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:49.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Excuse me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:50.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:55.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, you young girls would like\Nthese instead of rice crackers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.21,0:20:57.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.51,0:21:03.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Tarts, macarons, bavarois... Grandma,\Nthere's so much we can't eat all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.85,0:21:05.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.97,0:21:11.19,Main,,0,0,0,,So good! Tastes so good! All of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.65,0:21:16.03,Main,,0,0,0,,That's good. Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0},\Nyou have such a wonderful friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.82,0:21:25.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Now I'm recharged. Well, see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.37,0:21:27.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.87,0:21:36.46,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know WIXOSS\Ntoo well yet, and it's a bit scary,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:42.51,Main,,0,0,0,,but I owe it all to you for making Grandma happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:47.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Ru-{\i1}chan{\i0}, dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.31,0:21:51.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Coming! Um, I want to show\Nyou something, Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.69,0:21:53.77,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.77,0:21:59.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I made one more new friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.28,0:22:00.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Her name is Tama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.24,0:22:14.04,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nodding to the clockwork shadow{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.04,0:22:19.84,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}opens the door to the end,{\i0}\N{\i1}bringing in the darkness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.84,0:22:25.64,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There we catch glimpses of the perilous answer{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.64,0:22:31.56,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Today's prayer becomes taboo tomorrow{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.56,0:22:37.23,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The upside-down maze reflects{\i0}\N{\i1}the heavens and the earth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.23,0:22:43.15,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The gear begins to turn{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.15,0:22:49.33,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Listen carefully among the masses{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.33,0:22:59.25,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that bell resounding in{\i0}\N{\i1}the skies beckons the soul...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.59,0:23:06.68,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must move forward even beyond eternity{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.68,0:23:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because it is the future I chose{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.27,0:23:18.36,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The unreachable summer clouds{\i0}\N{\i1}and flickering heat haze{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.36,0:23:25.11,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One day I'll get back my place of smiles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:34.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.33,0:23:37.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.08,0:23:38.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Tama!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:39.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Please battle with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.84,0:23:41.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Urazoe Iona?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:44.63,Main,,0,0,0,,P-Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.63,0:23:47.01,Main,,0,0,0,,"That Poisonous Meeting."
